#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:0.5"
msgid "59. Vikappanasikkhāpada"
msgstr ""
"<hgroup><h1 id=\"Bu-Pc.59\">Monks’ Confession 59: the training rule on "
"transfers</h1></hgroup>"

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"nidana\">Origin story</h2>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.59.1\">Bu-Pc.59.1</a><a class=\"pts-vp-en\""
" id=\"BD.2.411\">BD.2.411</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1133</a>At one time the "
"Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā upanando sakyaputto bhātuno saddhivihārikassa "
"bhikkhuno sāmaṃ cīvaraṃ vikappetvā appaccuddhāraṇaṃ paribhuñjati."
msgstr ""
"At that time Venerable Upananda the Sakyan had transferred a robe to a monk "
"who was his brother’s student. He then used that robe without that monk "
"having relinquished it."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi—"
msgstr "That monk told the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:1.4"
msgid ""
"“ayaṃ, āvuso, āyasmā upanando sakyaputto mayhaṃ cīvaraṃ sāmaṃ vikappetvā "
"appaccuddhāraṇaṃ paribhuñjatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Venerable Upananada is using a robe that he had transferred to me, even "
"though I have not relinquished it.”</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:1.5"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1134</a>The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:1.6"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized Upananda,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:1.7"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando sakyaputto bhikkhussa sāmaṃ cīvaraṃ "
"vikappetvā appaccuddhāraṇaṃ paribhuñjissatī”ti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“How can Venerable Upananda use a robe that he had transferred to another "
"monk, when that monk has not relinquished it?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:1.8"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, upananda, bhikkhussa sāmaṃ cīvaraṃ vikappetvā "
"appaccuddhāraṇaṃ paribhuñjasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Upananda, that you do this?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:1.9"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:1.10"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:1.11"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, bhikkhussa sāmaṃ cīvaraṃ vikappetvā "
"appaccuddhāraṇaṃ paribhuñjissasi."
msgstr ""
"Foolish man, how can you use a robe that you had transferred to another "
"monk, when he has not relinquished it?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:1.12"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:1.13"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="rule">
#. REF: sc3
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:1.14"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhussa vā bhikkhuniyā vā sikkhamānāya vā sāmaṇerassa vā "
"sāmaṇeriyā vā sāmaṃ cīvaraṃ vikappetvā appaccuddhāraṇaṃ paribhuñjeyya, "
"pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pannatti\">Final ruling</h2>\n"
"<p class=\"rule\"><a class=\"wt-pa\">1135</a>‘If a monk himself transfers "
"robe-cloth to another monk, to a nun, to a trainee nun, to a novice monk, or "
"to a novice nun, and he then uses it without it first being relinquished, he "
"commits an offense entailing confession.’”</p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc4
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pada\">Definitions</h2>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.59.2\"></a><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-"
"Pc.59.2.1\">Bu-Pc.59.2.1</a><a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.412\""
">BD.2.412</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1136</a><term>A</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "<gloss>whoever …</gloss>"

#. HTML: </b><b class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "<term>Monk</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""
"<gloss>… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order "
"through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

#. HTML: </b>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc5, pts-vp-pli4.122
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.6"
msgid "Bhikkhussāti"
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.122\">Vin.4.122</a><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1137</a><term>Another monk</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.7"
msgid "aññassa bhikkhussa."
msgstr "<gloss>a different monk.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.8"
msgid "Bhikkhunī nāma"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1138</a><term>A nun</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.9"
msgid "ubhatosaṃghe upasampannā."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>she has been given the full ordination by both Orders.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.10"
msgid "Sikkhamānā nāma"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1139</a><term>A trainee nun</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.11"
msgid "dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhā."
msgstr "<gloss>one training for two years in the six rules.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.12"
msgid "Sāmaṇero nāma"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1140</a><term>A novice monk</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.13"
msgid "dasasikkhāpadiko."
msgstr "<gloss>a male training in the ten training rules.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.14"
msgid "Sāmaṇerī nāma"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1141</a><term>A novice nun</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.15"
msgid "dasasikkhāpadikā."
msgstr "<gloss>a female training in the ten training rules.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.16"
msgid "Sāmanti"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1142</a><term>Himself</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.17"
msgid "sayaṃ vikappetvā."
msgstr "<gloss>after transferring it himself.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.18"
msgid "Cīvaraṃ nāma"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1143</a><term>Robe-cloth</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.19"
msgid "channaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ vikappanupagaṃ pacchimaṃ."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>one of the six kinds of robe-cloth,<span class=\"note\" hidden>The "
"six are linen, cotton, silk, wool, sunn hemp, and hemp; see <span class=\""
"ref\">MS.3.1595</span>.</span> but not smaller than what can be transferred.<"
"span class=\"note\" hidden>This means not smaller than 8 by 4 standard (<i "
"lang=\"pi\">sugata</i>) finger-breadths, or 16 by 8 cm; see <span class=\""
"ref\">Kkh.</span> and BMC I, pp. 565-566.</span></gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.20"
msgid "Vikappanā nāma"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1144</a><term>Transfers</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.21"
msgid "dve vikappanā—"
msgstr "<gloss>there are two kinds of transfer:"

#. HTML: </b>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.22"
msgid "sammukhāvikappanā ca parammukhāvikappanā ca."
msgstr "transfer face-to-face and transfer in the absence of."

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.23"
msgid "Sammukhāvikappanā nāma"
msgstr "<a class=\"wt-pa\">1145</a><term>Transfer face-to-face</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.24"
msgid "“imaṃ cīvaraṃ tuyhaṃ vikappemi itthannāmassa vā”ti."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>one should say, “I transfer this robe-cloth to you/to so-and-"
"so.”</gloss>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.25"
msgid "Parammukhāvikappanā nāma"
msgstr "<a class=\"wt-pa\">1146</a><term>Transfer in the absence of</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.26"
msgid "“imaṃ cīvaraṃ vikappanatthāya tuyhaṃ dammī”ti."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>one should say, “I give this robe-cloth to you for the purpose of "
"transfer.”"

#. HTML: </b>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.27"
msgid "Tena vattabbo—"
msgstr "The other should ask,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.28"
msgid "“ko te mitto vā sandiṭṭho vā”ti?"
msgstr "“Who is your friend or companion?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.29"
msgid "“Itthannāmo ca itthannāmo cā”ti."
msgstr "One should reply, “So-and-so and so-and-so.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.30"
msgid "Tena vattabbo—"
msgstr "The other should say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.31"
msgid ""
"“ahaṃ tesaṃ dammi, tesaṃ santakaṃ paribhuñja vā vissajjehi vā yathāpaccayaṃ "
"vā karohī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“I give it to them. Please use their property, give it away, or do as you "
"like with it.”</gloss></gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.32"
msgid "Appaccuddhāraṇaṃ nāma"
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1147</a><term>Without it first being "
"relinquished</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.1.33"
msgid ""
"tassa vā adinnaṃ, tassa vā avissasanto paribhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>if it is not given to him or he uses it without taking it on trust, "
"he commits an offense entailing confession.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p>
#. REF: sc16
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.2.1"
msgid "Appaccuddhāraṇe appaccuddhāraṇasaññī paribhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"cakka\">Permutations</h2>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.59.2.2\">Bu-Pc.59.2.2</a><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1148</a>If it has not been relinquished, and he perceives that it has not, "
"and he uses it, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.2.2"
msgid "Appaccuddhāraṇe vematiko paribhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it has not been relinquished, but he is unsure of <a class=\"pts-vp-en\" "
"id=\"BD.2.413\">BD.2.413</a> it, and he uses it, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.2.3"
msgid "Appaccuddhāraṇe appaccuddhāraṇasaññī paribhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it has not been relinquished, but he perceives that it has,<span class=\""
"note\" hidden>MS here reads <i lang=\"pi\">appaccuddhāraṇasaññī</i>, which "
"must be an editing mistake. I instead follow the PTS reading, <i lang=\"pi\""
">paccuddhāraṇasaññī</i>.</span> and he uses it, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.2.4"
msgid "Adhiṭṭheti vā vissajjeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1149</a>If he determines it or gives it away, he "
"commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.2.5"
msgid "Paccuddhāraṇe appaccuddhāraṇasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it has been relinquished, but he perceives that it has not, he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.2.6"
msgid "Paccuddhāraṇe vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it has been relinquished, but he is unsure if it has, he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.2.7"
msgid "Paccuddhāraṇe paccuddhāraṇasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If it has been relinquished, and he perceives that it has, there is no "
"offense.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc18
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"anapatti\">Non-offenses</h2>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.59.2.3\">Bu-Pc.59.2.3</a><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1150</a>There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.3.2"
msgid ""
"so vā deti, tassa vā vissasanto paribhuñjati, ummattakassa, ādikammikassāti."
msgstr ""
"if the other person gives it or he uses it after taking the other person’s "
"property on trust; if he is insane; if he is the first offender.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc19
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc59:2.3.3"
msgid "Vikappanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
"<hr><p class=\"endsutta\"><a class=\"wt-pa\">1151</a>The ninth rule, the "
"training rule on transfers, is finished.</p>"
